Constructor Detail

LedgerEntry

public LedgerEntry(int type,
                   java.lang.String desc,
                   java.util.Date date,
                   double amount,
                   boolean credit)
Creates a new ledger entry.

Parameters:
type - denotes the entry type (LedgerEntry.PRINCIPAL, LedgerEntry.INTEREST or LedgerEntry.FEE)
desc - description of entry (e.g. "Monthly fee")
date - post date for an entry
amount - dollar amount of the entry (unsigned)
credit - specifies if the entry is a credit or a debit

getAmount

public double getAmount()
Returns the signed amount of the entry. Positive is entry is credit and negative if entry is a debit. This allows a sum of the entries to determine the current balance.

Returns:
signed amount
